Ad Text:
Are you ready to be part of an organisation that values expertise, passion and diversity? At CFS we know that the foundation of our success lies in our exceptional people. We believe in celebrating individuality, have a passion for high performance and creating an environment where you can unleash your full potential. Our people enable us to make a difference and deliver exceptional experiences to help our customers achieve financial freedom.

Your Team

The Manager, Retirement Data Strategy reports to Senior Manager, Retirement Strategy and is part of CFS's Superannuation and Investments business unit. This role will help shape the future of retirement strategy by embedding data-driven insights into member communication and guidance and Support CFS's mission to help Australians achieve financial freedom by delivering actionable intelligence for regulatory compliance, product design and customer engagement.

Your Responsibilities


Design and enhance retirement modelling frameworks and methodologies to evaluate member outcomes and guide strategic decisions.

Create and refine cohort approaches and advanced predictive models (e.g., Retirement Customer Lifetime Value) to anticipate member behaviours and needs.

Oversee the development of retirement dashboards and key performance indicators that enable data-driven management insights.

Continue to enhance Retirement Confidence Scores and outcome measures, leveraging member surveys and behavioural analytics.

Conduct industry research to identify and adopt innovative, market-leading data analytics and modelling tools, such as retirement calculators and projection platforms

Your Capability and Experience

Proven experience in data strategy, analytics, or modelling within financial services.

Strong technical expertise in predictive modelling, segmentation, and customer analytics.

Proficiency in data analysis tools (e.g. Tableau, Power BI) and programming languages (e.g., Python, R, SQL, Excel).

Familiarity with regulatory reporting (e.g., APRA) and compliance frameworks.

Strategic mindset with an innovative approach to leveraging data for understanding member needs and generating insight-driven support and guidance for super fund clients.

Knowledge of retirement, superannuation, or wealth management products and related regulations in Australia.

What to Expect

At CFS, you'll be working among the very best in the wealth management industry. It's an inspiring environment that encourages development and celebrates success. Other things to look forward to:

Access to CFS Employer Super, which offers an expansive investment menu and flexible insurance solutions

Support with financial services, including discounts on home loans and daily bank accounts through our partnership with a leading financial institution

Access to 24/7 confidential support covering safety, medical and mental health services

Life Leave - 3 days per annum to focus on your wellbeing or celebrate a special event

Exclusive discounts on retail, travel and entertainment

Additional leave day to celebrate your birthday



CFS Culture

At CFS we are committed to creating a thriving environment where individuals can flourish. We believe that success is built upon strong teams, and we are dedicated to celebrating uniqueness, championing individuality and supporting a diverse and inclusive workforce. We believe that when you can truly be yourself, you can unlock your full potential.

Apply today and join us in helping Australians to achieve their financial freedom.

Please note, CFS requires all candidates to have full work rights in Australia.

Where we have preferred candidates, background checks (including Police, Employment, Bankruptcy checks, ASIC banned and disqualified persons) will be completed prior to the final preferred candidate's employment being confirmed. The outcomes of the background checks do not preclude the preferred candidate, however, they will be assessed against the inherent requirements of the role.

This role is based on Gadigal Land (Sydney).

Data Warehouse Technical Lead | Power BI, SSIS/SSAS & Azure DevOps Step into a hands-on technical leadership role where you’ll sustain, enhance, and deliver enterprise-grade data warehousing and analytics capabilities. You’ll lead data modelling and integration efforts, uplift performance and governance, and work closely with stakeholders to turn reporting needs into robust, scalable solutions.


Location: Canberra, ACT (Hybrid)
Contract Duration: 12 + 12 months (extension option)
Security Clearance Requirement: Must hold a current NV1 clearance
Closing Date: 10:00am Friday 23 January 2026

Essential Tasks
Lead data warehouse sustainment and delivery across a complex enterprise environment
Design logical/physical models (dimensional schemas) and SSAS Tabular models
Build and maintain ETL integrations using SAP Data Services and Microsoft SSIS
Develop Power BI dashboards (DAX/semantic models) and uplift CI/CD via Azure DevOps/Git

Key Criteria
5+ years in large-scale data warehousing (ETL, dimensional modelling, optimisation)
Strong SQL Server ecosystem skills: SSIS, SSAS, plus Power BI and Azure DevOps (Git/CI-CD)
Proven leadership: mentoring, standards, stakeholder engagement, delivery ownership
Experience working in large government environments

How to Apply

Does this role sound perfect for you? If so, to register your interest in this role, please either contact Brendan Ly or the Compas Team on (02) 6230 0233 and send through your CV by following the link below.


About Compas:

Compas Pty Ltd is a Canberra based wholly Australian owned, Recruitment and Services company that has been operating since 1987. We specialise in the provision of permanent, contract and temporary recruitment services, as well as specialised Consulting assignments.


YOUR APPLICATION WILL BE TREATED WITH THE STRICTEST CONFIDENCE

Due to the nature of this environment, candidates must hold a current NV1 clearance.

Senior Data Engineer

10-month fixed-term contract - Potential to extend
Marsden Street, Parramatta (hybrid working available)

About Uniting

Our purpose: To inspire people, enliven communities, and confront injustice.
Our values: Compassionate, Respectful, Imaginative, and Bold

At Uniting, we take real steps to make the world a better place. Our focus is always on the people we serve, wherever they are in life.

We deliver services across aged care, disability, child and family services, community services, and chaplaincy, alongside strong social justice and advocacy work. We celebrate diversity and welcome all people regardless of lifestyle choices, ethnicity, faith, sexual orientation, or gender identity.

Uniting is the services and advocacy arm of the Uniting Church NSW & ACT. Our leaders understand, support, and can articulate the mission and purpose of the Uniting Church.

About the role

As a Senior Data Engineer, you will design, build, and maintain scalable, secure, and high-quality data platforms that enable analytics, reporting, and advanced data use across Uniting.

Working within the Data Engineering Chapter in the Data & Analytics team, you will collaborate closely with data analysts, data architects, and business stakeholders. You will provide technical leadership, contribute to architectural decisions, and help uplift data engineering practices to support informed, data-driven decision-making across the organisation.

This role is a 10-month fixed-term contract and reports to the Chapter Lead – Data Engineering, within the Property, Finance & IT directorate.

Key accountabilities

In this role, you will:

Integrate diverse data sources to create trusted, accessible datasets
Architect and implement solutions to support large-scale data processing
Automate data ingestion, transformation, and delivery workflows
Create Power BI Dashboard for Executive oversight
Create detailed reporting to support operational decision making
Monitor system performance, identify bottlenecks, and implement improvements
Apply best practice in data security, access controls, and compliance
Provide technical leadership through code reviews, mentoring, and design guidance
Evaluate and adopt new tools and frameworks to enhance data engineering capability

About you

You are an experienced, hands-on data engineer who thrives in complex environments and enjoys partnering with both technical and non-technical stakeholders. You bring strong problem-solving skills, a collaborative approach, and the confidence to guide technical outcomes while remaining pragmatic and delivery-focused.

As a staff member at Uniting, you actively support diversity and inclusion, working in ways that reflect our values.

Your capabilities

Individual leadership

Takes ownership of outcomes and delivers with a proactive, “can-do” mindset
Works collaboratively to improve performance and ways of working
Remains resilient and focused when navigating complexity
Plans and delivers work within agreed timeframes

Business acumen

Understands Uniting’s objectives and how this role contributes to them
Applies organisational values to day-to-day decision-making
Analyses problems, seeks input where appropriate, and implements effective solutions
Builds strong relationships and influences outcomes without direct authority

Qualifications and experience

Essential

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Information Technology, Systems Engineering, or a related discipline, or equivalent professional experience
10+ years’ experience designing, developing, and supporting data engineering, reporting, and analytics
Strong proficiency in Python, SQL, DAX, and Power BI
Proven experience designing and managing ETL/ELT pipelines
Solid understanding of data modelling, governance, quality, and security
Experience working with non-technical stakeholders, demonstrating strong communication, empathy, and insight
Proficiency with Git or similar source control tools
Ability to quickly learn and apply new tools and technologies

Highly regarded

Experience with cloud data platforms, particularly Microsoft Azure (e.g., Azure Data Factory)
Experience with Snowflake, including schema design, performance tuning, and secure data sharing
DevOps and automation experience (e.g., Python scripting, API integration, automated releases)
Exposure to predictive analytics, machine learning, or statistical techniques (Python/R)

Enquiries are welcome, please email Louise Massie at mmassie@uniting.org 




Click here to learn more about our great benefits: Benefits of working at Uniting 




Uniting NSW.ACT contributes to the work and mission of the Uniting Church in NSW and the ACT through social justice advocacy, community services, and spiritual care.

 We provide care and support for people through all ages and stages of life, with a focus on people experiencing disadvantage and vulnerability. Our purpose is to inspire people, enliven communities, and confront injustice.

Uniting is a Child Safe Organisation committed to promoting the safety, well-being, and inclusion of children and young people.

Empowered by diversity
At Uniting, inclusion isn’t just something we value – it’s how we work. Our culture and practice reflect the vibrant diversity of our colleagues, and the clients and communities we serve.

Senior Business Analyst (Contract) - Hobart
Location: Hobart

Rate: $900-1100 per day inc super
Duration: 6 months (plus extensions)
Working rights: must be an Australian permanent resident or Australian Citizen

Our Client

A large, complex organisation undertaking multiple technology and cyber-focused transformation initiatives. The environment is enterprise-scale, highly regulated and focused on improving resilience, security and modernisation across critical platforms and services.

Key Responsibilities

Plan and lead end-to-end business analysis activities across IT and business projects
Facilitate workshops and interviews to elicit, validate and prioritise business and technical requirements
Document current-state and future-state processes, business rules, dependencies, risks and constraints
Develop and maintain requirements traceability, managing change and impact assessment
Contribute to options analysis, concept briefs and business cases to support informed decision-making
Support procurement activities, testing phases and benefits realisation tracking
Collaborate closely with business, technical and project stakeholders to deliver clear, actionable insights
Review and assure project documentation to ensure quality, accuracy and alignment to intended outcomes

Required Experience

5+ years' experience as a Business Analyst within IT or enterprise project environments
Strong capability across structured business analysis planning and execution
Proven experience working across infrastructure, cyber, end-user computing or platform-based initiatives
Skilled in producing high-quality analysis artefacts (process models, requirements, RTMs, options papers)
Confident workshop facilitator with strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills
Experience supporting delivery phases including procurement, testing and change governance

Why Apply

Work across multiple high-impact technology and cyber initiatives
Join a mature project environment with strong governance and clarity of purpose
Opportunity to influence solution design, resilience and long-term capability outcomes
Collaborative, outcome-focused delivery culture with exposure to complex enterprise challenges

If this is of interest, please apply or send your CV to karim.romdhane@precisionsourcing.com.au and we'll be in touch if your CV has been shortlisted.

Job Title: Director, Multiple Opportunities - Data Governance, Data Strategy and Delivery
Company: Australian Transaction Reports and Analysis Centre (AUSTRAC)
Category:
Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
AUSTRAC is hiring two positions to join the Data Strategy and Collections branch, where our focus is strengthening the agency's enterprise data governance strategy, and maximising the value of our data in achieving regulatory and intelligence priorities This recruitment process will be used to fill current vacancies and build a merit pool for future roles. 

These Director roles offer a unique opportunity to help shape major enterprise shifts and uplift data culture and literacy across AUSTRAC. As a key data leader of the Data Division, your specialist data expertise and oversight across data capability initiatives will cultivate AUSTRAC's data governance strategy and culture. 

Be part of our transformation journey as we evolve into a world leading data-driven, digital agency in financial regulation and intelligence. If you embrace challenges diligently, are passionate about leading teams in a collaborative environment, and are eager to make a meaningful impact we encourage you to apply. 

Director, Data Strategy and Delivery 

You will be responsible for the coordination, alignment and delivery of AUSTRAC's strategic data capability initiatives to support data integrity, continuous enhancement and seamless integration. Your role is critical in ensuring high-quality, consistent data is available within AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence functions. You will influence and guide various stakeholders in integrating data outcomes in portfolio projects, while instilling best practice data governance and management principles. As a decisive and people-focussed leader, you will nurture a high-performing team of data professionals to deliver high-quality, operational data capabilities which are critical to support AUSTRAC's regulatory and intelligence operations. 

Key duties include: 

Design, develop and maintain AUSTRAC’s data initiatives and plans to ensure accurate and consistent data is available for AUSTRAC’s regulatory and intelligence functions. 
Product management of strategic data initiatives to align with AUSTRAC’s Reform and Transformation priorities, ensuring effective risk managemnet, governance pracices and sustainability. 
Lead cross-functional teams to design and deliver data plans and other strategic initiatives within cloud-based data integration architectures—including ETL and streaming processes, APIs, and data warehouse systems, and facilitate the democratisation and sharing of data with internal and external partners. 
Collaborate with various stakeholders to elicit business needs and design strategic data solutions that enable their use in analysis, business intelligence, and data science; overseeing the translation of these into data plans, projects, and initiatives. 

Director, Data Governance 

Your focus will be establishing and ensuring adherence to AUSTRAC's data governance frameworks, with the goal of optimising the use and flow of data whilst ensuring our data is safe and secure. Your role will be pivotal in managing controls to drive actionable data for intelligence, regulatory operations, and corporate needs. You will serve as a point of escalation for governance, data quality and protection issues and will work closely with agency leadership to improve the quality and value of core data assets. As a trusted, governance leader, you will build agency-wide understanding of data governance and lead a high-performing team to embed these practices across the agency.  

Key duties include:  

Lead the design, implementation and continuous improvement of AUSTRAC’s enterprise data governance framework, including AI governance and assurance activities, ensuring alignment with whole-of-government requirements and responsible use of AI and automated systems. 
Oversee stewardship and data lifecycle practices across the agency to ensure data is well managed, high quality, and fit-for-purpose.  
Oversee the AI Impact Assessment process and provide strategic advice on emerging data and technology risks. 
Oversee governance of AUSTRAC’s data sharing arrangements, MOUs and access frameworks to ensure compliance with legislative and policy obligations. 
Represent AUSTRAC in whole-of-government data governance forums and contribute to cross-agency initiatives that require coordinated data management and policy alignment. 
Prepare high-quality briefings, plans and risk assessments for senior executives and governance committees, and support uplift in data literacy and responsible data practices across AUSTRAC. 

For more information about the role and the capabilities where looking for, please refer to the Candidate Pack on the AUSTRAC Careers Page

Affirmative Measures

This vacancy is also being advertised concurrently under both general and affirmative measures recruitment processes.

Applications made under affirmative measures are only available to affirmative measures indigenous applicants or affirmative measures disability applicants.

Evidence will be requested if your application progresses under an affirmative measures process.

Notes

This recruitment process will initially be used to fill a current vacancy and in future, may be used to fill similar positions in the event positions become vacant. The merit pools established from this recruitment process will be valid for 18 months from the date of advertising.

We offer competitive remuneration and great conditions, including:

Annual leave of 4 weeks (20 days) per year + additional paid Christmas close down.

·       Cultural, Ceremonial and NAIDOC leave.

·       18 days of paid personal leave per year.

·       15.4% superannuation, which continues through paid parental leave.

·       18 weeks of paid parental leave.

·       Competitive APS salaries with access to annual salary progression.

·       Study assistance - up to $6,000 per annum and up to 120 hours of study leave.

View the AUSTRAC Enterprise Agreement for more information about current salaries and other conditions of employment.

About Us

AUSTRAC, Australia’s financial intelligence agency and anti-money laundering and terrorism financing regulator, is undergoing a significant transformation to enhance its role in combating money laundering and terrorism financing. This includes proposed expansion of its regulatory regime and a broader digital transformation to support our growing agency. As we embrace these changes and grow, our focus is on fostering innovation, collaboration, and effective problem-solving within an inclusive and supportive work environment. At AUSTRAC, you’ll be part of a team dedicated to maintaining the integrity of Australia’s financial system and making a real impact in preventing financial crime.

Closing Date and further details 

Applications close at 11:30 pm on Sunday 25 January 2026

For enquiries, please contact: Louise 0427 508 769

Please note, we can only accept applications via the AUSTRAC Careers Portal.

Represent AUSTRAC in whole-of-government data governance forums and contribute to cross-agency initiatives that require coordinated data management and policy alignment. 
Prepare high-quality briefings, plans and risk assessments for senior executives and governance committees, and support uplift in data literacy and responsible data practices across AUSTRAC. 

For more information about the role and the capabilities where looking for, please refer to the Candidate Pack on the AUSTRAC Careers Page

Affirmative Measures

This vacancy is also being advertised concurrently under both general and affirmative measures recruitment processes.

Applications made under affirmative measures are only available to affirmative measures indigenous applicants or affirmative measures disability applicants.

Evidence will be requested if your application progresses under an affirmative measures process.

Notes

This recruitment process will initially be used to fill a current vacancy and in future, may be used to fill similar positions in the event positions become vacant. The merit pools established from this recruitment process will be valid for 18 months from the date of advertising.

We offer competitive remuneration and great conditions, including:

Annual leave of 4 weeks (20 days) per year + additional paid Christmas close down.

·       Cultural, Ceremonial and NAIDOC leave.

·       18 days of paid personal leave per year.

·       15.4% superannuation, which continues through paid parental leave.

·       18 weeks of paid parental leave.

·       Competitive APS salaries with access to annual salary progression.

·       Study assistance - up to $6,000 per annum and up to 120 hours of study leave.

View the AUSTRAC Enterprise Agreement for more information about current salaries and other conditions of employment.

About Us

AUSTRAC, Australia’s financial intelligence agency and anti-money laundering and terrorism financing regulator, is undergoing a significant transformation to enhance its role in combating money laundering and terrorism financing. This includes proposed expansion of its regulatory regime and a broader digital transformation to support our growing agency. As we embrace these changes and grow, our focus is on fostering innovation, collaboration, and effective problem-solving within an inclusive and supportive work environment. At AUSTRAC, you’ll be part of a team dedicated to maintaining the integrity of Australia’s financial system and making a real impact in preventing financial crime.

Closing Date and further details 

Applications close at 11:30 pm on Sunday 25 January 2026

For enquiries, please contact: Louise 0427 508 769

Please note, we can only accept applications via the AUSTRAC Careers Portal.

Ad Text:
A career at ASIC will broaden and deepen your already accomplished knowledge, skills and abilities. By working on cutting edge issues, you'll make a difference to our goals, Australia's economic reputation and wellbeing and your own career aspirations 

ASIC's Data & Analytics Technology team is seeking an experienced and highly capable Data Modeller to join their high performing team.

 

Sydney or Melbourne locations
24-month fixed term position
Salary from $163,970 to $181,284 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026 

 

The team 

ASIC's Digital, Data & Technology group delivers a broad suite of IT capabilities to support ASIC. We are currently driving major technology initiatives that will accelerate our transformation across key areas including virtualisation, data analytics, mobility, and cloud. The Data & Analytics Technology team underpins these efforts by providing essential services to our primary stakeholder, the Data & Analytics Office. 

 

The role

As a Data Modeller you will be responsible for translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable data models across conceptual, logical and physical layers. These models will underpin analytics, reporting and operational processes. Collaborating closely with data engineers, analysts and business stakeholders the Data Modeller will ensure that data assets are well-structured, standardised and fully aligned with established governance and quality frameworks.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Design and maintain conceptual, logical and physical data models to support development and enhancements across ASIC's data infrastructure, including but not limited to data lakes, application databases, and BI/analytics solutions.
Collaborate effectively with business stakeholders and application/solution teams to define requirements and document data transformations.
Conduct peer reviews of data models developed by team members and external suppliers to ensure quality and consistency.
Take on additional responsibilities and tasks as required, demonstrating flexibility and commitment to team objectives.
Work in a professional, positive and cooperative manner, modelling ASIC's core values of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork.

 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a data modelling professional who thrives on turning complex business challenges into elegant, scalable solutions. With deep expertise in data modelling tools and strong knowledge of relational and NoSQL technologies, you will bring both technical precision and strategic insight expertise. You will communicate with clarity, collaborate seamlessly across teams, while championing data governance and quality more broadly. Adaptable and values-driven, you will embody ASIC's principles of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork while delivering impactful outcomes.

 

In addition, you will have:

Proven ability to quickly interpret complex business requirements and translate them into logical and physical data models using industry-standard modelling tools.
Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with the capability to convey technical concepts clearly to non-technical audiences.
Extensive hands-on experience with ERwin Data Modeller for designing and maintaining data models.
Strong experience with relational and data warehouse design techniques and modelling methodologies (Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault 2.0, NoSQL).
Familiarity with cloud data platforms and technologies (e.g. AWS, Databricks).
Comprehensive knowledge of established data management principles, frameworks, and technologies.

 

Click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

 

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Job Title: Financial Analyst – Leasing and Revenue Analytics
Ad Text:
About the Role

This is a high-impact Financial Analyst role with genuine ownership, partnering closely with senior Leasing leaders to drive revenue, portfolio performance, and strategic decision-making across a large retail property portfolio.

What you’ll do:

Partner closely with the Leasing team and respective Regional Leasing Manager, owning the leasing performance of your assigned regions and driving initiatives that maximise revenue and portfolio outcomes.

Lead budgeting and forecasting for your regions, providing accurate assumptions, meaningful analysis, and proactive recommendations, utilising analytical skills, scenario modelling, and reporting tools in Yardi and Power BI to drive better outcomes.

Challenge assumptions, identify risks and opportunities, and provide clear recommendations to support decision-making at Regional and Executive level.

Deliver data-driven insights on key leasing metrics including occupancy, rent spreads, vacancy rates, and leasing performance to inform strategic decisions

Support and contribute to monthly Board and Executive reporting, ensuring insights are clear, commercial, and decision-focused

Take end-to-end ownership of Investor Presentation deliverables, working closely with senior stakeholders to ensure accuracy, narrative clarity, and readiness for external scrutiny

Drive budgeting and forecasting of third line revenue, including Media, ATM, Vending Machine, CML, and Vacant Shop Income, ensuring robust assumptions and reporting.

Drive continuous improvement through better utilisation of Yardi and Power BI, enhancing the efficiency, automation, and impact of reporting and analysis.

About You

2–4 years’ experience in financial or management reporting, ideally in Retail Property, but open to other asset classes.

Comfortable operating in a fast-paced, senior stakeholder environment, with the confidence to challenge constructively and influence outcomes.

Strong experience as a Finance Business Partner, ideally supporting Leasing and/or Property Operations teams to deliver commercial insights and performance improvements.

Proven background in Financial Analysis, with hands-on experience in budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis.

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence and present insights to senior leaders.

Experience working with large, complex data sets, translating detail into clear commercial insights.

CA/CPA qualified


Good to Have

Solid understanding of leasing performance metrics, including occupancy, rent spreads, vacancy rates, and leasing outcomes.

Experience contributing to Investor Presentations, Q&A materials, and verification reports, ensuring high-quality and accurate outputs.

Demonstrated ability to drive process improvements and automation through enhanced system utilisation and data-led analytics.

Advanced skills in Excel and Power BI — building dashboards, Scenario Models, and delivering actionable insights for senior stakeholders.


Note: We are not accepting applications from recruitment agencies for this role.

Optus is an Australian telecommunications company, delivering more than 11 million services to our customers every day across mobile, broadband, and digital solutions.

The Senior Business Analyst - CIAM will play a key role in shaping how Optus onboards, identifies, and authenticates customers across all channels. Sitting within the CIAM program and reporting to the Director, this role partners closely with specialists across identity verification, authentication, and customer data to translate complex business needs into clear requirements. You'll help turn regulations, policies, and strategic objectives into actionable project outcomes, ensuring strong controls, smarter processes, and a seamless, secure customer identity experience.

In this high‑impact position, you'll drive priority initiatives such as building end‑to‑end identity reporting to detect issues and strengthen compliance, as well as defining requirements for unified authentication and new centralised identity verification services. Drawing on strong analytical and technical skills, you'll provide insights that drive real improvement and support fraud prevention, customer protection, and operational excellence. This role offers broad exposure across Senior Management, Risk, Finance, Sales, Service, Product, Engineering, Customer Insights, and Marketing.

What you'll be doing

Lead multiple CIAM projects, ensuring requirements are well‑defined and aligned to business and customer needs.
Act as a key liaison between CIAM, IT, senior leadership, SMEs, and experience teams to design compliant and improved identity and authentication solutions.
Maintain up‑to‑date expertise in large‑scale customer identity verification and authentication, including industry trends and emerging practices.
Produce high‑quality analysis and documentation for high‑risk projects, including business requirements, use cases, scope matrices, future‑state designs, and UAT plans.
Oversee project governance by identifying identity‑related risks and compliance issues across initiatives.
Manage and maintain the CIAM risk register, ensuring risks are actively tracked, escalated when required, and visible to senior stakeholders.

What makes you perfect for the role?

Degree in business, computer science, or a related field.
5+ years' analytics expertise across data integration, visualisation, SQL, and large datasets.
Identity, authentication & risk knowledge, including credit risk and compliance reporting.
Strong project and stakeholder skills, with proficiency in MS Project, Visio, Excel, BI tools, and clear communication.
Excellent analytical, presentation, and problem‑solving skills, with strong interpersonal and influencing capability.

Optus is a place where we let you do you. We offer a range of benefits including:

Competitive remuneration and employee discounts. Make life easier (and more affordable) with $80 monthly credit and 25% off Optus products and unique shopping discounts with our retail partners.
Flexible working arrangements with opportunities to work three days in the office, two days remote or home.
Vibrant and collaborative office campus that includes cafes, convenience store, chill out zones, GP, post office, gym and on-site childcare centre.
Competitive leave policies, including additional 'Connected' days to focus on culture, family, health, community, or whatever's important to you.
We support growing families with inclusive, carer-neutral paid Parental Leave of up to 16 weeks.
Direct your own development and build future-ready skills with Optus U's industry-focused micro-credentials, developed with La Trobe and Macquarie Universities.
Build meaningful connections through employee-led networks and diversity initiatives including Culture Connect, Elevate Women, Disability Network and Express Yourself (LGBTQIA+).
Put your wellbeing first with free access to counselling and support services, 24/7 — in-person, by phone, SMS, or video.

Harvey Norman’s Information Technology Department’s core focus is to deliver innovative IT solutions by delivering crucial projects to achieve the strategic goals of the business.

We have recently embarked on a journey to streamline processes, reduce technological complexity, and boost efficiency within our people management systems. This initiative will improve people data management, compliance, visibility and analytics, productivity, and employee engagement for approximately 15,000 people across Australia and New Zealand.

About the role  

This is a fantastic opportunity to be part of a large scale, complex HCM transformation. Joining a multi-disciplinary agile team, working closely with Technology, WFM/Payroll and HR leads, you will be responsible for leading business requirements & process analysis, and developing & executing test scenarios, focusing on Dayforce Implementation on downstream systems. 

This is Full Time Maximum Term Contract for up to 12 months, with an ideal commencement date in the first week of February 2026.

You will;

Requirements Gathering: Assist the WFM/Payroll & HR lead and collaborate with stakeholders to review, gather, document, and prioritise business requirements related to Dayforce implementation impacts of any downstream systems.
Business Process Analysis: Assist the WFM/Payroll lead, HR lead and Technology SME’s in analysing existing and future state business processes of downstream systems, identify areas for improvement in alignment with Dayforce capabilities, project team and SI partner. Facilitate stakeholder meetings to drive requirements, consider alternatives and negotiate project outcomes within milestone timeframes.
Testing: Work closely with both the Dayforce and Technology leads to assist & execute SIT/End-to-End testing, including documenting integration & downstream system test scenarios, validating errors or adjustments to user stories/acceptance criteria test scripts.
Detailed Procedure Documentation: Work closely with internal Payroll, WFM, technology SME’s, project leads and SI partner functional consultants to contribute to & review detailed administrator procedures for using Technology related administration related to the Integration services and all downstream systems
Team Support and Collaboration: Foster cross-team collaboration to help project team members complete project tasks and produce deliverables. Participate in your team's operating rhythm and provide progress updates through agreed forums and channels.

About you  

You will have extensive experience as a Senior Business Analyst in a similar role, with a proven track record of successfully delivering large complex IT projects. You will bring strong analytical thinking and problem-solving skills, enabling you to lead workshops, guide discussions, and provide insightful analysis for your projects. You’ll also have a keen ability to identify opportunities for improvement and drive meaningful change.

You will also have: 

Experience working on HR/Payroll/WFM projects across any ERP
Experience in writing business and project documentation to support the implementation of technology solutions.
Excellent written and verbal communication, with the ability to effectively communicate with business stakeholders.
Knowledge of project management lifecycles and product implementation methodologies (waterfall, agile, hybrid).
Proficiency in asking insightful questions to uncover the underlying reasons behind stakeholder processes.
Strong ability to manage multiple initiatives simultaneously and prioritise competing deadlines.
Expertise in the management and execution of end-to-end system testing
Ability to partner effectively with the business to ensure outcomes align with business needs and objectives.
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business or Engineering.

This opportunity will provide: 

Access to Udemy, an online training platform with over 5,500 courses.
Experience working with an Iconic Australian Brand with global success in NZ, Asia, and Europe.
A supportive team environment that celebrates diversity and promotes a healthy work and family life balance. 
Opportunities to make discounted purchases on a great range of products and services.

Have we got your interest?  

Apply now to be considered to join our dedicated team.  

Please note that only people with the right to work in Australia should apply for this position.  

Recruitment Agencies – thank you for thinking of us, however we do endeavour to fill our opportunities through direct channels wherever possible. If we find that we do need agency assistance, we’ll be in touch.

Job Title: Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting
Ad Text:
Take hold of a monster opportunity and join our Finance and Tax team as a Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting. If you’re a good fit for this role and live in Brisbane, Sydney or Melbourne we’d love you to apply. 




Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As the Senior Manager - Finance Systems and Reporting, you will oversee the development, maintenance, management, and implementation of Finance and Tax technology, data strategies, roadmaps, automation reporting, and continuous improvement initiatives. You will drive alignment and improvement for all Finance and Tax platforms/systems, services and vendors ensuring they effectively enable the delivery of financial data and regulatory reporting.

Key aspects of the role include:

Finance Technology & Systems Management

Manage financial technology platforms and integrate with enterprise systems.
Collaborate with IT and Finance teams to enhance system functionality and ensure compliance with regulations.
Oversee configuration, development, vendor relationships, and continuous improvements.
Risk management and governance oversight, including 1st line risk responsibility.
Change management and system testing.

Data Management, Reporting & Analytics

Implement data strategies, ensuring accuracy and accessibility.
Lead data governance including the use of Power BI tools for reporting.
Compile ESG and climate data.
Improve data quality and automation in financial processes.
Ensure compliance with regulatory reporting.

AI & Automation in Finance

Identify and implement AI-driven financial forecasting and automation.
Develop AI models for risk assessments and financial optimisation.
Drive process automation in finance operations.

Stakeholder Collaboration & Leadership

Align technology strategies between finance, IT, and business leadership.
Ensure financial systems support business goals.

Innovation & Continuous Improvement

Recommend and implement emerging technology solutions.
Drive digital transformation initiatives.

Leadership

Manage a high-performing team and foster a strong team culture.
Maintain relationships with enablement teams and vendors.

This role is available as 12-month max-term/ secondment opportunity. This role is known internally as Senior Manager - Finance and Tax, Systems and Reporting.

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Financial Systems and Data Skills.
AI knowledge.
Relevant superannuation business experience, regulatory reporting, tax and accounting experience.
Project Management and agile software implementation.
Excellent problem solving, analytical and process development/improvement skills.
The ability to think strategically with a commercial focus and respond to emerging issues and develop appropriate strategies and plans.
Demonstrated experience leading and developing a high performing team.

About us

Our 2.3 million members trust us to take care of almost $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close Sunday, 25 January 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Advanced familiarity with Microsoft Fabric and cloud-based data platforms, preferably certified in DP-600 (Microsoft Certified: Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate) and/or DP-700 (Microsoft Certified: Fabric Data Engineer Associate)
Advanced expertise in Power BI for data visualisation and reporting.
Advanced expertise in SQL (advanced queries, performance tuning and functions).

Excellent understanding of data modelling and data visualisation principles.
Familiarity with SAP Business Warehouse (SAP BW) and working with SAP data structures.

Strong grasp of data governance, data quality, and security best practices.

Support continuous improvement in reporting, planning, and analysis workflows.

Strong analytical, modelling, and reporting skills using Excel and Power BI.
Experience with SAP, SAC, TM1, or equivalent FP&A systems.

Strong commercial acumen with the ability to translate data into business insights.
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills.
Highly organised, detail-oriented, and proactive with a “can-do” attitude.

Job Title: Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems
Ad Text:
Classification: Academic Level C
Salary package: $146,007 - $162,281 per annum plus 17% superannuation 

Terms: Full time, Continuing

Position Description and Selection Criteria: PD & PEWER Level C Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems.pdf



Position overview 

The Research School of Management in the ANU College of Business and Economics aims to create and share management knowledge that makes a difference to organisations and society. Nine academics with affiliations to our School are listed among the 2025 Stanford/Elsevier Top 2% Scientists.

To continue the current growth trajectory, we are seeking to recruit a Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the field of Business Information Systems. The successful applicant will conduct research of international standing and actively contribute to undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in the School. They will have a strong work ethic, a practical approach, and be passionate about the quality of their work. The successful applicant will join a strong team of academics who publish in top international journals and hold external competitive grants. The School and College provide an excellent research environment, including favourable teaching load and internal research support. 

The position is open to international applicants. The successful applicant must be available to commence work in Canberra, Australia by mid-2026. The successful applicant will be offered relocation assistance as per ANU Policy.

We have a strong equal opportunity culture. We encourage all applicants particularly, female, Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander applicants. 

For further information, please contact Associate Professor Ashkan Zarghami, E: ashkan.zarghami@anu.edu.au

College overview 

The Australian National University (ANU) is one of the world’s great universities, ranking 32nd in the 2026 QS World University Rankings. The Research School of Management sits within the ANU College of Business and Economics. The College educates the next generation of business leaders, professional economists and academics. Our graduates have the knowledge and skills to lead organisations, design public policy, and research the big issues of business and economy.

Located in the national capital, we engage deeply with the business and policy communities. Our academics lead public debate on the critical issues of our time through their research, which is both long term and strategic in focus. Our internationally diverse student body is evenly divided between undergraduate and postgraduate study, and we have a large doctoral program. Our alumni are found in the world's leading companies, policy agencies and universities. 

We strongly believe that the way in which we operate is defined by our Values and Behaviours and encourage you to apply if you are looking for a workplace that encourages respect, collegiality and excellence. 

The University actively encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. For more information on employment opportunities, contact our Indigenous Employment Consultant on indigenous.employment@anu.edu.au.

ANU values diversity and inclusion and believes employment opportunities must not be limited by socio-economic background, race, religion or gender. For more information about staff equity at ANU, visit https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity
